Interested in business? Hofstra ranks in the top 5% of the nation's best schools for undegraduate business majors (PayScale College Salary Report 2017-2018) and in the top 19% nationwide for mid-career salary for alumni with MBA degrees compared to all others with advanced degrees (PayScale College Salary Report 2016-17). If you have an interest in engineering, U.S. News &amp; World Report 2020 ranks Hofstra's undergraduate engineering program (non-doctorate) #32 in the US. Similarly, Hofstra places highly in communication and liberal arts. Ranked #7 Best College Radio Station in the Nation (The Princeton Review 2019) and Top 15 Best Music Schools (Billboard Magazine 2017), you'll get your start in journalism and communication studying from accomplished faculty in the industry.</p>

